\title{GeoPaletteR: Colour Space Conversions for Geospatial Raster Data}
\description{
Converts red-green-blue raster bands into fifteen colour spaces used in remote sensing, image segmentation and forestry, among them CIELAB, CIELUV, DIN99, Oklab, CIECAM02 and Jzazbz, with inverse transforms back to red-green-blue for four of them. Operations are vectorised over whole bands, so a scene is converted without looping over pixels, and the package is plain R with no compiled code and no required dependencies. Results track the 'GeoPalette' Python package, which stores intermediates in single precision where R has only double, so agreement is to that precision rather than exact; the tolerances are measured and documented. Colour appearance modelling follows Moroney and others (2002) for CIECAM02, Safdar and others (2017) \doi{10.1364/OE.25.015131} for Jzazbz, and Ottosson (2020) for Oklab.
}
